  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And when thou prayest, thou shalt not be as the hypocrites,.... As the Scribes and Pharisees; whose posture in prayer, the places they chose to pray in, and the view they had therein, are particularly taken notice of: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for they love to pray standing in the synagogues, and in the corners of the streets, that they may be seen of men. It was their usual custom to pray \"standing\"; nay, it is established by their canons. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"There are eight things, (says Maimonides (u),) that a man that prays ought to take heed to do; and the first he mentions is \"standing\"; for, says he, no man may pray  , \"but standing\"; if he is sitting in a ship, or in a cart, if he can stand, he must stand; if not, he may sit in his place and pray.'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Several hints of this custom there are in the Misna (w). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"On their fast days they used to bring out the ark into the streets-- , \"and they stood in prayer\", or praying; and caused an old man to go down before the ark, who was used to recite prayers, and he said them.'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Again (x), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"whoever , \"stood praying\", and remembered that any uncleanness attended him, he might not break off, but he might shorten.'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Yea, standing itself is interpreted of praying; for it is said (y), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"and Abraham rose up early in the morning to the place, where he stood,   , \"and there is no prayer but standing\";'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "though sometimes they prayed sitting, as David did, 2 Samuel 7:18 so it is said of R. Jose, and R. Eleazar, that , \"they sat and prayed\", and afterwards rose up and went on their way (z). So it was likewise customary to go to the synagogues, and there pray; and indeed they were places built and appointed for this purpose. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "though sometimes they prayed sitting, as David did, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 7:18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " so it is said of R. Jose, and R. Eleazar, that , \"they sat and prayed\", and afterwards rose up and went on their way (z). So it was likewise customary to go to the synagogues, and there pray; and indeed they were places built and appointed for this purpose. ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"Wherever there were ten Israelites, a house ought to be provided, in which they may go to prayer at every time of prayer; and this place is called a synagogue (a).'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hence some have thought, that not such places are here designed, but any assembly, or concourse of people gathered together upon any occasion; but such an interpretation will find no place, when the following things are observed. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"For ever let a man go, morning and evening, to the synagogue; for no prayer is heard at any time, but in the synagogue; and everyone that hath a synagogue in his city, and does not pray in it with the congregation, is called a bad neighbour (b).'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Again (c), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "continued...",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "continued...",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
