        "text": "Luke 18:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; Lightfoot, p. 292 f.; at other times, however, also in a kneeling posture, or prostrate on the ground. Therefore the notion of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "fixi, immobiles",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Maldonatus), is not implied in the simple ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἑστῶτ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., which, however, forms a feature in the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "picture",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; they love ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to stand there and pray",
        "children": []
      },
      {
