          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐν ταῖς γονίαις τ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πλ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".] not merely when they happen to be surprised, or intentionally allow themselves to be surprised (de Wette), by the hour for prayer, but also at other times besides the regular hours of devotion, turning the most sacred duty of man into an occasion for hypocritical ostentation.",
